																		Author Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1581620&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227419" alt="DarkStuff" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1581620)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;" >DarkStuff</a></span> <span class="odate time_1585854812 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Apr 2020 19:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4578523">
									

<p>2020 is the year of Wilson's Wildlife Solutions. Thank you to the following critters:</p>
<ul>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ellie3" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3656445); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3656445&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1585854812" alt="Ellie3" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3656445)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ellie3" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3656445); return false;">Ellie3</a></span></li>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/othellothecat" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3213383); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3213383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1585854812" alt="OthellotheCat" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3213383)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/othellothecat" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3213383); return false;">OthellotheCat</a></span></li>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1229263&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1585854812" alt="Roget" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1229263)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;">Roget</a></span></li>
</ul>
<p>Finally back up in the three critics range! I really loved writing a description of what the WWS headquarters actually looks like. It was one of my favorite parts of writing this. That, and Feather (and by the way, I would not have named a character Feather had I not known someone named Feather in real life). Oh, and Captain Schut. Damn, I just liked writing this whole thing, didn't I? Heheh! Also, recently there was a re-evaluation of the plot outline, seeing as I had begun to disregard the outline for the sake of certain scenes and progressions that were brainstormed <em>after</em> the initial writing of the plot outline. And way back when, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3487700&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1585854812" alt="Uncle Nicolini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3487700)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;">Uncle Nicolini</a></span> had written the beginning of a scene for this chapter. So, here is a deleted scene!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Deleted&nbsp;Scene?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Again!?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Life after the incident had been hectic at Wilson's, to say the least.</p>
<p>Between undergoing repairs, trying to regain the goodwill of the townsfolk, grieving the death of Sarah Gardner and some of the critters, cataloging all the remaining animals, and constant interviews from the FBI and the Supervisors, Tim was up to his neck in backlogged paperwork. Months of bills, newsletters, notices, and many other fire hazards had come to clog up the Wilson HQ.</p>
<p>Though paperwork sometimes crept upon him in the past, it had never gotten <em>this</em> bad. Tim used to be able to just pull a volunteer and assign them to sort everything out, but ever since the incident, everyone was working around the clock to bring Wilson's up to snuff. It was exhausting, backbreaking labor which left Tim with little energy to do paperwork. Maybe if he were&#8230; say, twenty years younger and good with paperwork&#8230;</p>
<p>&#8230; like Fae.</p>
<p>It was on a hot August morning after the daily staff meeting that he pulled her aside. The main hall was empty and silent save for the hum of a wall-mounted air conditioning unit.</p>
<p>&quot;Hey, kiddo.&quot; She smelled like sun lotion, Fae was ready to head outside.</p>
<p>&quot;What's up dad?&quot; Her father looked a bit anxious.</p>
<p>&quot;I just wanted to thank you for all the work you've been doing around here. I really appreciate it and it means a lot that you'd help your old man out so much&#8230;&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;It's okay. I think at this point I've lost all the weight I put on during grad school just from sweating so really it's no big deal, ha!&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;You look great as ever, my darling.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Thanks, dad.&quot;</p>
<p>There was a momentary silence in which Tim hesitated. Fae, knowing he wanted something, smiled down at her dad and let her shoulders rest.</p>
<p>&quot;So&#8230; what was it you needed from me?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Well, it's just that&#8230; I wanted to ask a favor from you.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yeah, sure. Do you want me to run into town and pick up lunch for everyone again?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;No, not today. Alice is making jambalaya for everyone. I wanted to ask you to, uh, handle some paperwork for me.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Oh, okay. What do you need done?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I'll just show you.&quot;</p>
<p>Tim sheepishly pointed towards his office and motioned for Fae to follow him, and the two set out.</p>
<p>&quot;Dad, you don't need to be embarrassed to ask me to do your financials for you. I already do them for mom, and I told you I would do them for you too.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;It's just-&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Dad, seriously.&quot;</p>
<p>Tim moved to open the door, which Fae held shut with her hand.</p>
<p>&quot;It's like you don't pay attention to me.&quot;</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

